<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If $3 is that big of a deal quit, please.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Perhaps it is a big deal to some people, and perhaps they don't want to quit. If they question the value of continuing their subscription in a civilized way, what do you care?<br>
<br>
Angry boneheads like you seem to want to jump down the throat of anyone who has a concern, as if it makes you look more manly for being rude to someone not &quot;macho&quot; enough to keep their ideas to themselves. <br>
<br>
I can deal with people who bitch because they usually have valid concerns, they just communicate them wrong sometimes. These holier-than-thou types that think they're proving something by obnoxiously yelling that JohnnyEQ's opinion is not worth anything, however, make me want to quit. Luckily, you tend to be few and far between.<br>
<br>
These forums have a lot of really intelligent people in them, and I for one appreciate that when an issue arises, I can come here and rely on all its implications and consequences to be fleshed out. If you had your way and no one made critical statements anymore, we'd simply be a bunch of sheep, repeatedly posting our manaburn screencaps and nothing more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukelvyntelarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelvyn Telarian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/25/02 9:37:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14682.topic&index=147>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> price increase</span><hr size=1> All Texas homeowners insurance went up statewide from 100-120% beginning this year. There is no alternative, no insurance company will give a rate at anything less. Since you can't have a mortgage without the insurance, you basically must pay.  As I understand, many states have had similar jumps; just another thing to consider. Insurance companies are trying to offset claims related to several massive losses in the past year, not the least of which was September 11.<br>
<br>
Another thing that always surprizes me is that people post analyses of VI's gross income and then try to extrapolate net profits without removing taxes. Considering this can be as much as 40% of earnings, it would be a more realistic assessment to remove these before trying to figure how rich they are.<br>
<br>
Finally, 15 million bucks on a corporate scale is a very minor amount of money, barely covering overall property increases, insurance, tax increases, salary increases (yes, their employees would probably like some kind of minor raise in 3 years), increases in some computer hardware (memory for example is back on the rise), etc. <br>
<br>
A 30% increase in cost &quot;all at once&quot; is not really very significant. Someone here was trying to argue that gasoline caused an uproar when it jumped too high, but gasoline is looked at against the total cost, not the percentage in jump. In otherwords, people only freak as it approaches 2 dollars US a gallon. In reality, it often jumps from 99 cents to $1.29 over a few week period and most people don't bat an eye.<br>
<br>
On a personal level, I probably will be cancelling one of my less played accounts, but I hardly think an increase like this is anything to take offense at. On a business level, I know they are gonna take a hit, at first, since a portion of their multi-account holders will drop secondary accounts. However, I am sure they know exactly how many multi-account holders they have, and they have calculated in an expected loss there. I am pretty sure most people will get over this in a month or two and add those accounts back. Desperately wanting to do a CR or gear swap with an alt or 2-boxed account at 3 AM has a powerful effect on one's ability to overlook 3 bucks.<br>
<br>
<br>
